Race_Origin_TEXT: Why are only Alaskans and Hawaiian or Pacific Islanders able to signify as native? I identify as Chicanx, claim no fealty to the spanish throne in any way, understand that the tribes of the Mexica do not encompass the totality of "mexicans", and have roots in the twice colonized indigenous people of the Americas. The delineation here seems more geopolitical than historical and I am curious as to why that is significant in this study, much less the distinction of whiteness to include the Germanic and Irish people who were at one time, not considered white but "swarthy". Why now are these arbitrary delineations changing, especially in a scientific perspective not only to broaden the inclusivity of whiteness, but to further stratify racialized groups? I would find it very interesting if you included both this common legal stratification of "race/origin" as well as one which is explicitly self-identified by each participant, to see the differences between how participants perceive their own identity and how they believe their identity is perceived through a legal framework, as per my own example.
